The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 CCI ropes in Rhodes

Mumbai: Jonty Rhodes will hold a three-day training camp at the Cricket Club of India (CCI) here from November 25-27. 

The retired South African cricketer will teach the finer points of fielding to youngsters in the camp. 

Fifteen boys from nine cricket associations affiliated to the BCCI are to take part in this unique endeavour, CCI president Raj Singh Dungarpur said in a media release. 

Apart from CCI, players from the associations of Mumbai, Vidarbha, Maharashtra, Gujarat, Saurashtra, Madhya Pradesh, Jammu and Kashmir and Punjab will take part in the camp, the release said. 

Former India captain Mansur Ali Khan Pataudi would be present during the clinic. 

 (PTI) 




